{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CrN1v5EmwWqvJA98wus6m9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is stable. Here's a summary of what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** The `health-overrides` ConfigMap had a stale entry `mongodb-replica-1: legacyHealthPass123`. The health-check script loads per-pod password overrides from this ConfigMap, so every probe on `mongodb-replica-1` (the PRIMARY) was attempting to authenticate with the wrong password, causing repeated `Authentication failed` probe failures.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n1. **`health-overrides` ConfigMap** — removed the stale `mongodb-replica-1: legacyHealthPass123` entry. The health check now falls back to the correct `healthpass123` password from the `health-user-password` secret for all pods.\n\n2. **Probe `timeoutSeconds` 5→10** — increased on both liveness and readiness probes in the StatefulSet to eliminate the intermittent timeout failures seen on `mongodb-replica-2` (mongosh startup + auth can push against a 5s limit).\n\n**Final state:**\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts\n- Replica set: 1 PRIMARY (`mongodb-replica-1`) + 2 SECONDARY (`mongodb-replica-0`, `mongodb-replica-2`)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":493,"cache_read_input_tokens":44353,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":493},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0ee47d13-fc9e-4599-ba2a-510e66c35c4c","uuid":"fbe55bb8-2720-4e5e-b9cb-0cbd963b6194","request_id":"req_011CcPsSx1FqeXMLBh2g94f8"}
